{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775892884242,"sessionID":"ses_2848c4100ffe5LtG4M55bByBGV","part":{"id":"prt_d7b750fe3001R6YimHSIhQphJQ","messageID":"msg_d7b750035001Ojns7bOTe7wK10","sessionID":"ses_2848c4100ffe5LtG4M55bByBGV","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:22","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-023/tasks.md","content":"# AR-023 — CLI invoke/status 命令\n\n> **AR ID:** AR-023  \n> **Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n> **Language:** Python  \n> **Size:** M  \n> **Stage:** ST-3 (Design) Completed → ST-4 (Implementation)\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nThe `invoke` and `status` CLI commands enable users to interact with deployed agents. The `invoke` command sends HTTP requests to agents with JSON payloads, while `status` retrieves the deployment state from either AgentCube (AgentRuntime CR) or Kubernetes (Deployment/Service) providers.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.1 — InvokeRuntime Implementation\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.1.1 | Create `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` with `InvokeRuntime` class | File exists with proper docstring and imports | 0.5h |\n| 4.1.2 | Implement `InvokeRuntime.__init__()` with verbose, provider, logger, MetadataService | Logger level set; service instantiated | 0.5h |\n| 4.1.3 | Implement `InvokeRuntime.invoke()` main entry point | Returns invocation result dict | 0.5h |\n| 4.1.4 | Implement `InvokeRuntime._validate_invoke_prerequisites()` | Returns Tuple[AgentMetadata, str, str] | 1h |\n| 4.1.5 | Implement `InvokeRuntime._invoke_agent_via_agentcube()` | Sends HTTP POST via httpx; builds correct URL | 1h |\n| 4.1.6 | Implement `InvokeRuntime._direct_http_invocation()` | Sends direct HTTP POST via httpx | 0.5h |\n| 4.1.7 | Implement `InvokeRuntime._build_k8s_endpoint()` | Constructs endpoint from k8s_deployment info | 0.5h |\n| 4.1.8 | Add session header injection (`X-Agentcube-Session-Id`) | Header added if session_id in metadata | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** InvokeRuntime can invoke agents via both agentcube and k8s providers.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.2 — StatusRuntime Implementation\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.2.1 | Create `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` with `StatusRuntime` class | File exists with proper docstring and imports | 0.5h |\n| 4.2.2 | Implement `StatusRuntime.__init__()` with verbose, provider, logger, MetadataService | Logger level set; service instantiated | 0.5h |\n| 4.2.3 | Implement `StatusRuntime.get_status()` main entry point | Returns status dict with required keys | 0.5h |\n| 4.2.4 | Implement `StatusRuntime._get_k8s_status()` | Queries Deployment/Service status via KubernetesProvider | 1h |\n| 4.2.5 | Implement `StatusRuntime._get_cr_k8s_status()` | Queries AgentRuntime CR via AgentCubeProvider | 1h |\n| 4.2.6 | Handle \"not_published\" status (no agent_id or k8s_deployment) | Returns proper status dict with message | 0.5h |\n| 4.2.7 | Handle \"error\" status (FileNotFoundError, API errors) | Returns proper error status dict | 0.5h |\n| 4.2.8 | Extract and return status fields: status, agent_name, agent_id, endpoint, provider, message | All fields present in response | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** StatusRuntime can check status via both agentcube and k8s providers.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.3 — AgentCubeProvider Extensions\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.3.1 | Add `AgentCubeProvider.get_agent_runtime()` method | Returns CR dict or None; handles 404 | 0.5h |\n| 4.3.2 | Add CR_GROUP, CR_VERSION, CR_PLURAL class constants | Constants defined correctly | 0.25h |\n| 4.3.3 | Handle kubernetes.client.exceptions.ApiException in get_agent_runtime | 404 returns None; others raise | 0.5h |\n| 4.3.4 | Extract status fields from AgentRuntime CR | status, agentEndpoint extracted | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** AgentCubeProvider can retrieve AgentRuntime CR status.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.4 — KubernetesProvider Status Method\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.4.1 | Verify `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status()` exists and works | Returns status dict with state, replicas, available_replicas | 0.5h |\n| 4.4.2 | Ensure status mapping logic: available == desired → \"ready\" | Logic correct | 0.25h |\n| 4.4.3 | Ensure status mapping: available < desired → \"pending\" | Logic correct | 0.25h |\n| 4.4.4 | Handle Deployment not found (404) → \"not_found\" | Returns proper status | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status() works correctly.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.5 — CLI Invoke Command\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.5.1 | Implement `invoke` command in `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Command registered with Typer | 0.5h |\n| 4.5.2 | Add `--workspace` / `-f` option (default: \".\") | Option works; path resolved | 0.25h |\n| 4.5.3 | Add `--payload` option (default: \"{}\") | JSON string accepted | 0.25h |\n| 4.5.4 | Add `--header` option (multiple allowed) | Headers parsed as \"key:value\" | 0.5h |\n| 4.5.5 | Add `--provider` option (default: \"agentcube\") | Values: \"agentcube\", \"k8s\" | 0.25h |\n| 4.5.6 | Add `--verbose` option | Enables DEBUG logging | 0.25h |\n| 4.5.7 | Validate JSON payload format | JSONDecodeError handled with red message | 0.5h |\n| 4.5.8 | Validate header format (must contain \":\") | Error message on invalid format | 0.5h |\n| 4.5.9 | Parse headers into dict | Headers dict passed to runtime | 0.5h |\n| 4.5.10 | Create InvokeRuntime and call invoke() | Runtime instantiated correctly | 0.5h |\n| 4.5.11 | Display success message with Rich JSON output | console.print_json(data=result) | 0.5h |\n| 4.5.12 | Handle errors via `_handle_error()` | Exits with code 1 on error | 0.5h |\n| 4.5.13 | Add Rich Progress spinner during invocation | Progress shown during work | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** CLI invoke command works end-to-end with proper UI.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.6 — CLI Status Command\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.6.1 | Implement `status` command in `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Command registered with Typer | 0.5h |\n| 4.6.2 | Add `--workspace` / `-f` option (default: \".\") | Option works; path resolved | 0.25h |\n| 4.6.3 | Add `--provider` option (default: \"agentcube\") | Values: \"agentcube\", \"k8s\" | 0.25h |\n| 4.6.4 | Add `--verbose` option | Enables DEBUG logging | 0.25h |\n| 4.6.5 | Create StatusRuntime and call get_status() | Runtime instantiated correctly | 0.5h |\n| 4.6.6 | Display status in Rich Table | Table with Property/Value columns | 0.5h |\n| 4.6.7 | Exit with code 1 if status is \"not_published\" or \"error\" | typer.Exit(1) on error status | 0.5h |\n| 4.6.8 | Handle errors via `_handle_error()` | Exits with code 1 on exception | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** CLI status command works end-to-end with proper UI.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.7 — Import and Wiring\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.7.1 | Import `InvokeRuntime` in `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Import at top of file | 0.25h |\n| 4.7.2 | Import `StatusRuntime` in `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Import at top of file | 0.25h |\n| 4.7.3 | Add `InvokeRuntime` to `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py` exports | Re-export from runtime package | 0.25h |\n| 4.7.4 | Add `StatusRuntime` to `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py` exports | Re-export from runtime package | 0.25h |\n| 4.7.5 | Ensure httpx is in project dependencies | Added to pyproject.toml | 0.25h |\n\n**Deliverable:** All imports work; dependencies installed.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.8 — Unit Tests — InvokeRuntime\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.8.1 | Write `TestInvokeRuntime` — initialization | Creates logger and MetadataService | 0.5h |\n| 4.8.2 | Write `TestInvokeRuntime` — validate prerequisites for agentcube | Returns metadata, endpoint, agent_id | 0.5h |\n| 4.8.3 | Write `TestInvokeRuntime` — validate prerequisites for k8s | Returns metadata, endpoint, agent_name | 0.5h |\n| 4.8.4 | Write `TestInvokeRuntime` — agent not published error | ValueError raised for agentcube without agent_id | 0.5h |\n| 4.8.5 | Write `TestInvokeRuntime` — missing router_url error | ValueError raised for agentcube without router_url | 0.5h |\n| 4.8.6 | Write `TestInvokeRuntime` — missing k8s_deployment error | ValueError raised for k8s without deployment | 0.5h |\n| 4.8.7 | Write `TestInvokeRuntime` — build k8s endpoint | Correct URL constructed from metadata | 0.5h |\n| 4.8.8 | Write `TestInvokeRuntime` — session header injection | X-Agentcube-Session-Id header added | 0.5h |\n| 4.8.9 | Write `TestInvokeRuntime` — invoke via agentcube | HTTP POST sent to correct URL | 1h |\n| 4.8.10 | Write `TestInvokeRuntime` — invoke via k8s | HTTP POST sent to endpoint | 1h |\n| 4.8.11 | Write `TestInvokeRuntime` — httpx error handling | HTTPStatusError propagated | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** InvokeRuntime tests pass with >80% coverage.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.9 — Unit Tests — StatusRuntime\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.9.1 | Write `TestStatusRuntime` — initialization | Creates logger and MetadataService | 0.5h |\n| 4.9.2 | Write `TestStatusRuntime` — get_status for agentcube | Returns status dict with correct fields | 0.5h |\n| 4.9.3 | Write `TestStatusRuntime` — get_status for k8s | Returns status dict with correct fields | 0.5h |\n| 4.9.4 | Write `TestStatusRuntime` — not_published status | Returns status=\"not_published\" | 0.5h |\n| 4.9.5 | Write `TestStatusRuntime` — error status (no metadata) | Returns status=\"error\" | 0.5h |\n| 4.9.6 | Write `TestStatusRuntime` — get_k8s_status ready | Status=\"ready\" when replicas match | 0.5h |\n| 4.9.7 | Write `TestStatusRuntime` — get_k8s_status pending | Status=\"pending\" when unavailable | 0.5h |\n| 4.9.8 | Write `TestStatusRuntime` — get_cr_k8s_status | CR status extracted correctly | 0.5h |\n| 4.9.9 | Write `TestStatusRuntime` — not_found_in_k8s status | Returns status=\"not_found_in_k8s\" | 0.5h |\n| 4.9.10 | Write `TestStatusRuntime` — API exception handling | Returns status=\"error\" on exception | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** StatusRuntime tests pass with >80% coverage.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.10 — Unit Tests — CLI Commands\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.10.1 | Write `TestCLIInvoke` — default options | workspace=\".\", payload=\"{}\", verbose=False | 0.5h |\n| 4.10.2 | Write `TestCLIInvoke` — workspace override | -f /path/to/agent passed correctly | 0.5h |\n| 4.10.3 | Write `TestCLIInvoke` — custom payload | --payload '{\"key\":\"value\"}' parsed correctly | 0.5h |\n| 4.10.4 | Write `TestCLIInvoke` — custom headers | --header \"Auth:Bearer token\" parsed correctly | 0.5h |\n| 4.10.5 | Write `TestCLIInvoke` — multiple headers | Multiple --header options work | 0.5h |\n| 4.10.6 | Write `TestCLIInvoke` — invalid JSON payload | Error message displayed, exit code 1 | 0.5h |\n| 4.10.7 | Write `TestCLIInvoke` — invalid header format | Error message displayed, exit code 1 | 0.5h |\n| 4.10.8 | Write `TestCLIInvoke` — provider selection | --provider k8s passed correctly | 0.5h |\n| 4.10.9 | Write `TestCLIInvoke` — success output | JSON result displayed | 0.5h |\n| 4.10.10 | Write `TestCLIInvoke` — error handling | Error message in red, exit 1 | 0.5h |\n| 4.10.11 | Write `TestCLIStatus` — default options | workspace=\".\", provider=\"agentcube\" | 0.5h |\n| 4.10.12 | Write `TestCLIStatus` — workspace override | -f /path/to/agent passed correctly | 0.5h |\n| 4.10.13 | Write `TestCLIStatus` — provider selection | --provider k8s passed correctly | 0.5h |\n| 4.10.14 | Write `TestCLIStatus` — not_published exit code | Exit code 1 when not published | 0.5h |\n| 4.10.15 | Write `TestCLIStatus` — error exit code | Exit code 1 on error status | 0.5h |\n| 4.10.16 | Write `TestCLIStatus` — table output | Rich Table displayed with status | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** CLI tests pass with >80% coverage.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.11 — Integration Tests\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.11.1 | Create `tests/integration/test_invoke.py` with fixtures | File exists with test workspace fixtures | 0.5h |\n| 4.11.2 | Test invoke with mock HTTP server | Request received with correct payload | 1h |\n| 4.11.3 | Test invoke with session header | X-Agentcube-Session-Id header present | 0.5h |\n| 4.11.4 | Test invoke with custom headers | Custom headers present in request | 0.5h |\n| 4.11.5 | Create `tests/integration/test_status.py` with fixtures | File exists with test workspace fixtures | 0.5h |\n| 4.11.6 | Test status for unpublished agent | Returns \"not_published\", exit code 1 | 0.5h |\n| 4.11.7 | Test status with mocked KubernetesProvider | Status returned from mock | 1h |\n| 4.11.8 | Test status with mocked AgentCubeProvider | Status returned from mock | 1h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Integration tests pass with real filesystem and mocked services.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.12 — Documentation\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.12.1 | Add module docstrings to `invoke_runtime.py` | pydoc shows documentation | 0.25h |\n| 4.12.2 | Add module docstrings to `status_runtime.py` | pydoc shows documentation | 0.25h |\n| 4.12.3 | Document `InvokeRuntime` methods with docstrings | Args, returns, raises documented | 0.5h |\n| 4.12.4 | Document `StatusRuntime` methods with docstrings | Args, returns, raises documented | 0.5h |\n| 4.12.5 | Update CLI command help text | invoke --help shows descriptions | 0.25h |\n| 4.12.6 | Update CLI command help text | status --help shows descriptions | 0.25h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Code is well-documented for maintainers.\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n| Phase | Tasks | Est. Hours |\n|-------|-------|------------|\n| ST-4.1: InvokeRuntime | 8 | 5h |\n| ST