entcube --cov-report=term-missing\n\n# Lint verification\nruff check agentcube/\nmypy agentcube/\n```\n\n---\n\n## Definition of Done\n\n- [ ] All 101 tasks complete\n- [ ] Package installs successfully (`pip install -e .`)\n- [ ] CLI commands work (`kubectl-agentcube invoke`, `kubectl-agentcube status`)\n- [ ] Unit tests pass (>80% coverage for each module)\n- [ ] Integration tests pass\n- [ ] Type checking passes (`mypy`)\n- [ ] Linting passes (`ruff`)\n- [ ] Documentation complete with docstrings\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- `typer[all]>=0.9.0` — CLI framework (already present)\n- `pydantic>=2.0.0` — Data validation (already present)\n- `pyyaml>=6.0` — YAML parsing (already present)\n- `rich>=13.0.0` — Progress indicators and tables (already present)\n- `httpx>=0.24.0` — HTTP client for invocations (NEW)\n- `kubernetes>=28.0.0` — K8s client (already present)\n- `pytest>=7.4.0` — Testing framework (already present)\n- `pytest-cov>=4.1.0` — Coverage reporting (already present)\n- `pytest-mock>=3.11.0` — Mocking utilities (already present)\n- `respx>=0.20.0` — httpx mocking for tests (NEW)\n\n---\n\n## Design Notes\n\n- **Provider selection:** `--provider` accepts \"agentcube\" (AgentRuntime CR) or \"k8s\" (Deployment/Service)\n- **Payload format:** JSON string passed to `--payload`, validated before sending\n- **Header format:** `\"Key: Value\"` format, parsed into dict\n- **Session header:** `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` automatically added if session_id in metadata\n- **Status exit codes:** Exit code 1 for \"not_published\" or \"error\" statuses\n- **URL construction for agentcube:** `{router_url}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n- **Error handling:** All errors use `_handle_error()` for consistent display\n- **Progress indication:** Rich Progress spinner during invoke operation\n- **Output formatting:** JSON for invoke, Rich Table for status\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnosti